Sales tax-risk management
Risk management in the Czech Republic
In the Czech Republic, several organizational units at different levels of financial management are concerned with risk management in the field of sales tax.
Within the Czech Ministry of Finance, the following organizational units are responsible for risk management and combating turnover tax fraud:
The Department for Methodology and Economic Management of Turnover Tax or its Risk Management Unit is concerned with identifying potential risk fields for tax volume and evaluating trends in these risks in domestic and intra-Community trade.
At national level, this body coordinates the criteria for "credibility of sales tax returns" and uses the MIAS data to discover possible tax evasion within the framework of intra-Community deliveries and acquisitions.
Based on data on the trade balance of the Czech Republic, it shall evaluate products that are at risk, prepare for risk management in the field of turnover tax and cooperate in this field with the competent EC bodies and the other Member States.
The Department for International Assistance in the Field of Turnover Tax shall ensure, inter alia, the exchange of information, shall contribute to the creation and transfer of a relevant information database, evaluate the data available in the MIAS system of other Member States, provide public relations and shall be responsible for other forms of intergovernmental assistance within the meaning of Council Regulation (EC) 1798/2003.
