The BRH found that the German financial officer did not correct the German acquirer's sales tax return, since a German court had confirmed the insolvency of the German taxpayer.
Since the previous external audit did not show any signs of tax fraud, there is no prospect of actually charging a fixed turnover tax liability.
20. According to the MIAS data, a German tax payer acquired in 2005 goods from the Czech Republic worth €4.251,196, according to which he had acquired goods worth €43,274 the previous year.
The German tax payer did not declare the intra-Community acquisition either in its sales tax return in 2004 or in that for 2005.
He also did not declare any value-based starting sales.
Because of these inconsistencies, the German FA made a request for information concerning 4. Quarter 2005 and 1. Quarter 2006.
